			<header id="header">
				<h1>BL Basic Security Indicator</h1>
				<p>Securing your infrastructure and applications is a continous process. If you want to improve your security level the first things you need to do is:

<ul>
 <li>Automatically Measure your security Level</li>
 <li>Rate your security level</li>
 <li>Manage your findings</li>
</ul>

First you need to measure - then you can manage. blbsi is a system to automatically calculate a security indicator of a (linux) system. It scans trough all your installed programs and checks configuration files for best practices or known security issues. If you are interested in running blbsi (which is still in beta testing) - please leave your email and we will get back to you shortly.

For more details - see <a href="how-it-works.html">how it works</a> or <a href="links.html">further links</a>.

</p>

<p>
The python code for the framework is developed by <a href="http://slash4.net">slash4.net</a> and can be downloaded from <a href="https://github.com/slash4-de"></a>
</p>
			</header>

